content: and welcome to Analysis lesson at ORC
today will be my last teaching session for few months
so I hope all will go nicely :)
We here in Finland do not have many players
in the 1st national Championship tournament we managed to gather only 6 players
this year we're hoping to attract few more players
not so many people in Finland
this year National Championship is closed I think
maybe next year we might invite foreign players to get bigger tournament
one of the first renju players in Finland was Lauri Toivonen
he and Marko Pellikka are from the same town as me
and they introduced me to the game
MArko has played in some WC qualification tournaments
and Lauri managed to qualify for European Championship final in 2002
they both have talent, but not so active anymore
Today we will watch a game from an Offlinea League in Finland played in 2003

endlessroad, luwenzhe, benben, derkas, Ikon, ouyang, tommy, callings, Iskander, YKS, LiuJianping, cloud, yboil, akira, mayhem, sunrain, xuwu, sosei, whywhy, Whiz, weigui, Timo, shuwang, ethereal, konjin, Laney, yzhnie, pantrike, Liuchao, YeYuwuziqi, iris, mima, tjlz_ax, yaya, casar, xinxin, kawamura.
some of you might recognize Lauri by username zathras from some online gaming sites
if you know him, you know also he prefers D3 opening
he is not so keen on theoretical positions
guest is not needed 'I AM HERE
in 2003 we often played this position
back then, we did not analyse much other than post-game analysis
What is your opinion on this position ?
white not bad, but still hard :)
Black can make some attach, but White should hold.
generally speaking, white is better here than black judging from game results
the difficulty in this position does not just concern black
it's easy to judge white being stronger, if black follows the move 16
black can not create much there, and white can control
why does this cause problems to white also
it also threatens some to connect top and bottom black stones
so, how to stop this connection ?
yes, i6 gives more power for white on right side
e7 is maybe an attempt to stop black from using move 15 as a connection point and tkaing over the left side
using i6 makes connecting sides much harder
therefore black should get power to lower side in order for this to work well
can black make strong attack purely on lwoer side ?
"play where the opponent would like to play" (Go saying)
yes, it often applies in positional play I think
black can attack g6, h5, later on connect k8
point h6 all in all is dangerous to give to white
is no use to take it :) hehe, nice
good konjin, you did find it :)
but black material is not very strong
so black is in trouble here, if not careful
it makes right side more and more strong
and here black doesn't have much chances to start a direct attack
if black has to defend right side,
so black must attack on left side
26 can even be at j5 maybe
back then, I did not know this weakness
but as you saw, white can afford to attack
Lauri reacted to this, maybe seeing the danger
black might be able to keep tempo and move to upper part
I as usual played again a safe defence
it seemed that with 23 he wanted to keep my possible counter on line E under control
what can you say of black attack now ?
but no idea where to extend
black damaged his chances on upper and left side
white must block vcf threat in the lower part
I chose to close black to a tight area
what do you think, does it hold ?
i did not find that bw
as you ask, you have a trap somewhere :D
I can not see black winning
and if possible there might be an outside 28, which would maybe be better
I did not find black win here
but I still chose inside move
but it is not so good
black attack is dead on left side
it seems white is clear now
because this was offline game, there was time to think
but we had a 7day move rule
and I was away for many days here
when I got back, I played here quickly
I was thinking, white really should win here
we did not have too many days left in timie
so I made a move here
knowing my opponent, I knew he did not expect such move
because it has no meaning really :)
then I was out of material :)
but I thought Lauri will think I have a trick on my mind
and by this I killed more his time
I needed a win from this game to win the league
after 35 I was worried I might have to struggle in end
so I made up some tricks
with 38 I hoped to make a small battle on lower side
Lauri made a series to kill my time
and then made a spacious defence on right wing
I had a plan on upper side
but I wanted still to play some time killer
how much time do you have for the game?
so I played such position to board
starting from 36, I was only killing Lauri's time
so I could win the game on upper side
why did I choose this tactics ?
because I could not find sure win for me
I knew i12+g11 is nice attack
and 38 was the only essential move for this in the series
I knew Lauri would find it, if enough time given
so I had to kill most o fit before coming here
I did not find win here
and here my tactics paid off
and this is what I met when I analysed after 35
so, this game is actually a tactical lesson
though I made a weaker move at 20
and played a safer choice at 28
i still did not get it how you won
it was a tricky position after 66
but I had counted it should be enough
seems I am poor as an entertainer, most sleeping :)

akira, konjin, whywhy, Whiz, luwenzhe, benben, endlessroad, derkas, Iskander, danfengyue, mayhem, YKS, Ikon, weigui, casar, Liuchao, YeYuwuziqi, tjlz_ax, xuwu, ouyang, Laney, iris, cloud, pantrike, sosei, sunrain, yzhnie, mima, callings, shuwang, LiuJianping, hallo, xinxin, kawamura, yboil, yaya, verne, ethereal.
this was a game from Finland, a lesser known renju nation
you learned about a bit odd tactics
but as most of you know,
in offline game you can choose various streategies
you taught well, so we don't need to ask a lot
to say were they best choices, is not necessary
it is important to know your opponent
most of the time, you do it by analysing his opening
a useful way is also to learn his style of thinking
with 36 I exploited my idea of Lauri's mind
it along with 52-58 killed the necessary time
for me to win with a position that is not sure win
he probably could've seen the saving pattern
this win was sadly not enough for me anyway
Lauri finally won me by 1 point in the round
but atleast I got to say I beat the winner :)
this game did not offer much new things
but the variation of 16 is interesting
with this 17th black has definitely choices
maybe it is necessary to go there :)
here the right side is terrifying
how the game could go for 19 e7
so now white can't be so active
this lesson is over, thank you for attending
